          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2019-04-04T16:54:44Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Border Wall Trust Fund Act</b></p> <p>This bill authorizes the Department of the Treasury to accept gifts of money for constructing, designing, or maintaining a barrier on the U.S.-Mexico border. Treasury shall establish the Border Wall Trust Fund to store the funds and a public website to receive such gifts. Such funds shall be appropriated for the border barrier and may not be used for any other purpose.</p> <p>The Department of Homeland Security shall provide for a commemorative display recognizing individuals who contributed to the Trust Fund. The display shall be part of the border barrier.<br> </p> <p><br> </p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2019-01-03T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
